## Benefits of Agentic AI

### Parallelism (Superhuman Speed)

Human cognition is fundamentally sequential. Agentic workflows run tasks **asynchronously**:

1. Generate multiple search queries **simultaneously**
2. Download and read all resulting web pages **at the same time**
3. Synthesize data into a final output

> Even though agentic workflows take longer than a zero-shot prompt (more steps), they are drastically faster than a human doing equivalent research.

<!-- [image3: Parallelism diagram — insert here] -->

### Modularity (The "Lego Block" Architecture)

Non-agentic AI is a black box — prompt in, answer out. Agentic workflows are **modular**: complex tasks are broken into atomic steps you can swap on the fly.

- **Swapping Tools:** If Google Search isn't returning good results, swap the agent's tool to GitHub or Stack Overflow instead.
- **Swapping Models:** Use a cheap, fast model (e.g., Llama 3) for search term generation, and a heavier model (e.g., Claude Sonnet or GPT-4) for the final output.

### Massive Performance Gains (Workflow > Scaling)

The industry used to believe bigger = better. Agentic workflows prove this wrong.

**HumanEval coding benchmark results:**

| Approach | Score |
|---|---|
| GPT-3.5 Zero-shot | 40% |
| GPT-4 Zero-shot | 67% |
| GPT-3.5 **Agentic** (draft → test → reflect → rewrite) | **>67%** |

> **Key Insight:** You don't always need the most expensive frontier model. Wrapping a cheaper model in an intelligent workflow can achieve state-of-the-art results at a fraction of the cost.

